<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
My zombie Hobbit got the black breath from fighting a ringwraith. I deleted the character in anger without thinking! I'm not the only one doing so... <p>
Is the resistance to black breath Hobbits are supposed to have limited to classical hobbits? Why did I get black breath at every opportunity if I have at least resistance(I'm not expecting immunity)? 
</p>
<p>
Hobbits have the best ability bonuses total (searching, trap detection, magic device, etc) in the game. This alone might be worth it in older versions. The -10 melee and low hit dice (7) will hurt warriors who don't pick zombie to sort of compensate... but in 2.3.0 most racial ability bonuses are gone so Hobbits are *WEAKLINGS* with no compensation better than their +5 luck! And the cooking skill that helps you not starve where monsters don't drop corpse(experienced players don't need cooking - newbies can't use it yet). 
</p>
<p>
The sling skill bonus looks nice, but slings are NEVER VERY POWERFUL at least in 2.2.7 (even artifact ones). 
</p>
<p>
Bandobras: They say, magic device ability only applies to rods and activations in 2.2.7. They also say, black breath resistance is only a resistance, not the immunity. I would like it changed, too. <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
Simon: Hobbits being what they are, they should get some kind of bonus or be considered for extra score for playing an "expert" race. 
</p>
